title: For Sale:  **Smith & Wesson 66-1** (4" with box)
postcontent: For sale is a very nice vintage Smith and Wesson model 66-1 (pinned barrel and recessed cylinder) with a 4" barrel. This is a K-Frame, .357 combat magnum revolver that also has the capability of shooting .38 speicals as well. Included with this gun is the original box, instruction manual, and VCI paper. This is the twin to the Smith and Wesson model 19; only in satin stainless steel. This is a very sought after model with collectors, especially with having the pinned and recessed features and the durable stainless finish. The gun was shipped from the factory sometime around 1979 with a serial # of 42K94xx. This 66 is unmolested; not all highly polished to make it shine like many you will find are from this era. It is in outstanding overall condition with a very faint turn line and very few handling marks. I would rate it at an easy 98%. Timing and lockup of the cylinder are both spot on; very tight. The forcing cone is in excellent condition with no erosion/cracks; virtually no flame cutting on the top strap. This has a plain blackened rear sight blade with red ramp insert on the front sight. The grips are correct, genuine Smith and Wesson K-Frame targets with speedloader cut-out indicative of the year. The label on the box corresponds with serial number and all features mentioned. This is quite a nice package not seen very often. Price is $850.ABSOLUTELY NO SHIPPING!!!Local Face-to-Face transaction in the area.Looking for a WI resident with a valid WI ID. title: For Sale:  **Smith & Wesson .357 Magnum / Pre-27** (5-screw)
postcontent: For sale is a Smith & Wesson .357 magnum revolver (aka the Pre-model 27) with the uncommon 6.5" barrel. This gun has rich, deep bluing that Smith and Wesson was well known for during this time period. The ship date on this was in 1955, with a serial # of S1358xx. The condition of this gun is very good; I would rate it at about 95%, considering it is 62 years old. The finish is all original with no re-work stampings. It has the pinned barrel with recessed cylinder on a 5-screw frame. This N-Frame Smith features a gorgeous checkered top strap, .500" target hammer, and the Patridge front sight with "proud pins." The stocks are not original to the gun, however it comes with a nice set of smooth presentation grips with nice grain. The barrel and cylinder are numbered to the gun from the factory. Timing and lockup of the cylinder are excellent. The action is simply amazing on this one, like butter in both single/double action. The revolver has a minor turn line, very faint muzzle wear, and a few handling marks throughout. The cylinder also has a slight "plum" color to it under certain light, however I've read this was due to the bluing process on these older Smith's. This is gun only, no box. Please feel free to E-mail with any questions or request additional photos.
